                        h2 Sun, Sea & Smiles: A Stay at Hyatt Ziva Los Cabos
                        h3 A Brief Overview and Beachfront Location
                        p Hyatt Ziva Los Cabos is an all-inclusive beachfront resort located along the gorgeous Sea of Cortez on the Baja California Peninsula in San José del Cabo, Mexico. Perched where desert dunes meet sweeping ocean vistas, this resort is designed for travelers of all ages and blends spectacular natural beauty with laid-back Mexican charm. It’s situated just a short drive from downtown San José del Cabo and roughly 25–30 minutes from Los Cabos International Airport, making it a convenient and scenic base for a memorable Cabo vacation.
                        p This expansive resort welcomes families, couples and groups with spacious suites — many featuring private balconies with uninterrupted ocean views — plus a myriad of dining, entertainment and poolside experiences, all wrapped into one inclusive package.
        section.features
            .container
                .row
                    .col-12
                        h3 Highlights & Why It’s Special
                        p All-Inclusive Fun for Everyone
                        p Hyatt Ziva Los Cabos is a full all-inclusive resort, where meals, drinks, entertainment and many activities are included in the room rate. From casual beachside snacks and oceanfront dinner venues to top-shelf beverages and specialty cocktails, every day feels effortless and enjoyable.
                        p Diverse Dining & Drinks
                        p The resort features 8 restaurants and 7 bars and lounges, offering everything from gourmet cuisine and teppanyaki to casual fare and poolside bites. Wine and tequila sommeliers help elevate the culinary experience with curated tastings.
                        p Beautiful Beach & Pools
                        p Guests enjoy direct access to a pristine stretch of beach on the Sea of Cortez as well as multiple swimming pools — including an infinity pool, adults-only pool with swim-up bar, and kid-friendly zones. Private cabanas around the pools and beach offer a relaxed way to soak up the sun.
                        p Entertainment & Activities
                        p Whether you’re traveling with family or friends, there’s plenty to keep everyone engaged: daily activities like water aerobics, beach volleyball, yoga and cooking classes; nightly live entertainment; and water slides and playground spaces in the KidZ Club for younger guests.
                        p Spa & Wellness
                        p The on-site Zen Spa offers a peaceful sanctuary inspired by the natural elements, with massage and beauty treatments that help you unwind after a day in the sun.
                        p Fitness & Recreation
                        p Stay active with a large, modern fitness center — one of the most extensive in Los Cabos — offering cardio and strength equipment plus areas for yoga, Pilates and more.
                        p Events & Celebrations
                        p With over 35,000 sq ft of versatile meeting and event space, Hyatt Ziva Los Cabos is also a compelling choice for weddings, corporate retreats and special celebrations, all backed by beautiful coastal scenery and full resort amenities.

